elf writing as much as 20 pages of story a month, last time I did this I clocked about 250 written pages, 500 if in paper-back format <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br><br><br>The cool, clean breeze of the ocean swept through the long, brown hair of Winlabik.  Looking out across the vast amount of water, he saw small spots of fishing trawlers, trying to get to port before the storm.  Down closer to the horizon, Win could make out the dark silhouette of the clouds, making their way closer to the coast.<br>His Brown-Green eyes focused in on another small spec, what looked like a child in the water!  Holding up his binoculars, he zoomed in on the object.<br>&quot;Just another piece of driftwood.&quot;  He said to himself, putting his glasses back down.<br>Shifting slightly in his seat, he picked up his receiver.  &quot;Control, this is nine-zero-five-alpha.&quot;  He checked his code book for a few words, &quot;No visual on Frisbees, looks like a clean slate.&quot;<br>He stood up and started to collect his belongings into a small bag, his fisherman's chair still planted into the sand.<br>&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Roger, nine-zero-five-alpha,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; the radio reported back, &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Clear the area and head for hangover.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>Win knew the command the second he heard it, the storm was going to be rough, and he needed to head for shelter.<br>Pulling a small map out of his pocket, he started to finger a route to the town hall.  After a few minutes of looking at the map, he placed it back into his pocket and picked up his chair.<br>'<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Good thing I didn't drive here,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->' he thought, '<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   my car would have been left out for the storm...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'<br>Walking up the sandy beach, he checked back over his shoulder, the storm was getting closer and the waters were becoming clear of traffic.  It was going to be one hell of a night.<br><br><br><br>((When you speak out of character, or OOC, use these parentheses to show it.  You should have a general idea of what the story is about, it takes place in a small coastal town, and there is a hurricane about to hit.  Have fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ))<br><br>((PS: To prevent people posting at the same time, first post a message that looks like this:<br><br>((I'm writing the next post now))<br><br>Then edit that post with the writen post as soon as you are done, but don't take more than 15 minutes!  Consider that as a bookmark for you spot as the next writer.))<br><br>EDIT: Forgot to mention, turn off your sigs and personal photos. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A> at: 7/20/01 3:12:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usaphiresphere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphire Sphere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/20/01 2:28:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1>   Although the sees were becoming turbulent Saphire knew he was going to make it back to Spheres. He had promised her he would come home, that his love of exploration would not overcome his love for her. <br>  &quot;Excuse me, sir. Should we batton down the hatches and prpare to row in? It would take longer but it would be safer.&quot;<br>  &quot;No, its ok for now. Keep the sails intact and await your orders, Tes.&quot; Saphire was in no mood to wait he had been gone to long. He could barely here her voice anymore. He had to be back as soon as possible! He just needed to be. &quot;I'm going to my cabin don't disturb me, unless something is seriously wrong.&quot;<br><br>   &quot;Something must be troubling my master because he isn't talking to the crew anymore. He's not even talking to me and he always talks to me. I can see it in his saphire eyes. His heart is broken. I must get my master home soon, before the storm gets much worse.&quot;<br>   &quot;Alright men lets get there NOW! We can feel the storm coming in with the way this boat is rocking. Its just a matter of time before it catches up with us and capsizes the boat!&quot;<br>   And with Tes' orders the whole boat sprang to life. Everyone tieing everything down and making sure that the sails didn't flap to violently. THe winds were getting worse and they needed to hurry. And that's when One Eye spotted it. The massive twister coming towards them. They were all doomed at sea. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usaphiresphere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphire Sphere</A> at: 7/20/01 2:39:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicchaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gothic chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/20/01 2:42:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> whoo,this thing is getting underway,i'm writing now<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicchaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gothic chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/20/01 2:57:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> Liz sighed. She hated being dragged outside of her natural enviroment,and the beach was certainly not natural to her. In the water,splashing around were 6 people she called her 'friends.' Though the word meaned nothing to her than just someone to talk to besides her parents. Liz went back to her book that was titled &quot;Myths of the Norsemen&quot;. She had gotten a few odd looks when she had brought the book to school. No one her age read that sort of thing.<br>'None but Odin and has wife and queen Frigga were priviliged to use this seat-'. She sensed the twister befor she saw it. Her head snapped up from the pages of her book straight to the funnel.<br>&quot;uh guys,&quot;She shouted to her friends who splashed merrily in the water unaware of the uncoming twister.<br>&quot;yeah?what is it liz?&quot;one of them shouted back. Liz pointed in the direction of the twister.<br>&quot;we had best go before-&quot;<br>&quot;hey!thats pretty cool!we can watch it as we swim!&quot; The youngest of them all,Carrie was her name,shouted.<br>&quot;that wouldn't be safe!Its coming right for us,if we don't hurry,well...&quot;Liz trailed off. She'd rather not go into detail for fear that her gory explaination would disturb them.Five of her friends trudged out of the water,but Carrie,being as stupid as she was,floated there gazing at the twister.Her other five friends picked up their things and hedded towards the nearest building. Carrie started to move towards the shore,and Liz stood up,sure that the danger had been averted. After a moment of walking her body went stiff. She looked back,but Carrie wasn't there as she had suspected. Floating in the water was a pale blue body,face down bobbing slowly in the water. Liz blinked. The body was gone,and in its place was Carrie,still staring at the twister. <br>&quot;Carrie,move it or-&quot; <br>     Carrie went under. Her head bobbed back up,gasping for air. Liz's nerve snapped. Her mind darted back to that horrible instant in the lake when she had been 9. She could feel the ice cold water stabbing like a thousand neddles on her flesh. The sour taste of the water as she gulped-. Carrie screamed. Liz looked around her. The other had gone in. She couldn't go in the water!Carrie was to far out and liz would surely drown if she entered the water. She did the only thing she could think of.<br>&quot;somebody help!Theres someone in the water!Somebody!We need help!!&quot; She continued shouting,shivering with fear.<br>'oh god..please let someone come..'<br>&quot;HELP!&quot;<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/20/01 3:07:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> Winlabik put his chair up against the side of the town hall; he looked to the sky for a moment.  The sky was still clear directly above, but to the west he could hear it coming.  The sound of a freight train, something he was quite aware of.  He had chased storms before joining the &quot;Corps&quot;, so he knew his weather when he heard it.<br>&quot;Sounds like a funnel over the water,&quot; he said to himself, as he checked his equipment once more.<br>Pulling out the radio microphone he tapped down on the button, &quot;Nine-zero-five-alpha, I've hit hangover.&quot;<br>&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Rodger, five-alpha.  Wait the storm out.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>&quot;Understood control, nine-zero-five-alpha out.&quot;  He placed the mike back into his gym bag and recollected his stuff, it wouldn't be long now until the storm would hit.  Luckily, the Town Hall had a shelter under it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A> at: 7/20/01 3:13:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uravenofmemory.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenofmemory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/20/01 6:22:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> ((*big big grin* Heh...roleplaying happens to be my most major hobby, it's really how I got into writing in the first place...there are thousands of great clubs, with all sorts of different settings, on Yahoo Clubs, I'm in about a dozen of them ^_^))<br><br>Ed McArthur sat on the front porch of his house; the home was weather-beaten from years of exposure to the sea, sun and salt air, and had a toughened, scarred feel to it. Ed had the same appearance. With a perpetual rough salt-and-pepper five o'clock shadow and stringy, shoulder-length silver hair with some strands of black, he looked like he'd been through hell and had given more than he'd got. In addition to this, he was over six feet tall, and his limbs were so thin and bony that he seemed a giant when seen without other objects to put scale to him.<br><br>He'd lived in the same house in the town since anyone could remember, only emerging once a week to buy groceries and every day in the morning to tend his small garden. He had no friends, no-one he played cards with; no-one even knew whether or not he had a phone, and if he did, his number was unlisted.<br><br>But, whatever his background, whatever his worldview, he sat on his porch and watched the twister approach; then, the desperate shouts of Liz drifted up from down the beach and he turned his head in a birdlike motion and listened.<br><br>He stayed in his seat for another moment or so after he understood the meaning of the cries for help, then made a silent decision and rose from his seat, his spidery limbs unfolding as he ran down the beach to where Carrie was drowning, kicking up sand...<br><br>As he drew up to Liz, he stopped, breathing slightly hard. &quot;What happened? She a friend of yours?&quot; he asked in a gruff voice, then saw how close the twister was coming and saw that there was no time left to assess the situation...and, that unless he acted right then, Carrie had no time left to her either.<br><br>The recluse ran into the surf, not bothering to take off his shirt; he was barefoot, a good thing since shoes make swimming twice as hard. Swimming with powerful strokes, showing more strength than would have been expected from his thin frame, he quickly caught up to Carrie, and grabbed her around the neck, fighting the undertow.<br><br>Holding her with one arm, he frantically strove to make it back to shore, to water that he could stand in...with the strokes of an expert swimmer, albeit one that was somewhat rusty, he strained back to shore, fighting the current that would drag him and the girl into the twister and leave nothing more than their bloated and blackened bodies, no souls, no lives...<br><br>With a final heroic effort, he gained the shore, standing unsteadily and staggering out of reach of the waves, supporting Carrie before falling to one knee, coughing from the water that he had accidentally swallowed in the rough surf.<br><br>((Hope this is OK....^_^ I like spectacular character entrances!)) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uravenofmemory.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenofmemory</A> at: 7/20/01 6:28:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uravenofmemory.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenofmemory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/20/01 6:27:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> ((Eep, forgot to disable the photo thingy...it's disabled now tho ^_^)) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/21/01 2:55:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> &quot;&quot;Welcome, Sir.&quot;  A smiling face greeted Winlabik as he hit the bottom of the stairs.  &quot;Coffee and blankets are over there, please help yourself.&quot;<br>Smiling back, Win nodded his head slightly and found a spot to drop his stuff.  There were maybe 20 others in the shelter with him.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  'Strange,'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> he thought, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  'this can't be the whole town...'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>He shrugged his shoulders to himself and went to the coffee machine.  Control had him up late last night, as with just about every other night.<br>What had started as another sighting just turned into nothing but simple light flashes from a storm cloud just over the horizon.  Almost as much of a failure as the one mission where a guy claimed to have bodies.<br>Winlabik grinned when he started to remember tapping on those hard bodies, made from paper-mache.  After he left Duke University with his Psychology degree and Minor in Parapsychology, Win joined up with the &quot;Corps'.  A group devoted to the scientific study of the Paranormal.  In the course of his, so far, three-year professional career, he had seen just about everything.  Although it seems easier to trace down Ghosts and Psychics than what he was in Waatch for, UFOs.<br>Control was the central office, they tried to keep themselves moving fast, very similar to his earlier job of storm tracking.  If there is a report of anything, usually a Corps member is no more than 2 hours away from the sighting.<br>Fixing up his coffee, Win noticed that the others were looking pretty upset.  Understandable since they have homes and possessions out in that storm.  Lucky for him, he was just visiting.<br>Win licked his small plastic stirrer and then sat back down on the floor next to his things.  Pulling out his journal, he started to record the day's failure.<br>'Welcome to Waatch, Washington.&quot; He said to himself. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A> at: 7/21/01 2:56:14 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicchaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gothic chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/21/01 1:47:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=le