ste of seawater.<br><br>&quot;Euch...eh? Yeah, yeah, I'm all right...You're right, that twister looks like it's still getting closer and the storm's only going to get worse from now on.&quot;<br><br>He followed her pointed hand and nodded. &quot;Yeah...I heard something on the radio about there being a storm shelter underneath the building. I just hope it'll hold...this looks like it'll be a really bad one. Let's go...you need any help carrying your friend? She looks kinda heavy...&quot;<br><br>He started walking towards Liz and the Town Hall beyond her, ready to lend the strength of his arms to supporting Carrie and helping get her, as well as the two of them, to shelter.<br><br>&quot;By the way, I'm Edward...Ed McArthur.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usempaisloan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SempaiSloan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/22/01 11:02:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> Deuce slapped the palm of his hand against the greasy linoleum floor. He could hear the old man's breathing. The old man was panicking. Hell, maybe he'd have a cardiac or something. Maybe Deuce wouldn't have to betray his own position with a gunshot.<br><br>Deuce leaned back on his feet, and peered out from behind the stainless steel kitchen fridge. The front of the restaurant was darker than it was ten minutes ago. Clouds were rolling in from the sea.<br><br>He heard a rattle from the restaurant. The old man must have bumped into some silverware. The raspy breathing paused for a second, but resumed with greater enthusiasm. Deuce felt a smirk crawl over his lips. The old man was afraid.<br><br>Deuce slid out from under the counter and snaked around the island in the kitchen. In the distance he heard thunder, and something... louder. Noise was good. He could take the shot without worrying about nosey podunk neighbors.<br><br>He paused by the closet. The old man was starting to cough. Deuce heard him clear his throat.<br><br>&quot;All... all right.  You come out of there, now! I'm only a warnin' you this one time. You hear?  Step outta there. I got me a gun!&quot;<br><br>Deuce shook his head. Damned old fool. From the sound of his voice, he was closer to the kitchen door.<br><br>He took a look around the island. He found two dusty leather boots standing beside the door way. The thunder outside was increasing. And that roar! <br><br>Must be a tornado.<br><br>Damn.<br><br>Deuce pushed his feet against the cabinet, and shoved. He slid along the linoleum and drew a bead on the old man.<br><br>With a single shot, he emptied the man's head onto the wall.<br><br>Lightening strikes were getting closer. Deuce didn't want to hang around waiting for some overweight sheriff to pick him up for looting and find the mark dead in his own restaurant.  But he couldn't just hole up in this weather.<br><br>The best place to hide would probably be with the rest of the herd.<br><br>Deuce darted out the back door into the stinging mist flying in from the beach. In the distance, he saw a small group of young people barreling for the town hall. <br><br>He tucked his 9mm into his shoulder holster, pulled his collar up, and ran for the town hall, as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/22/01 1:14:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.t