ileptic episode, but without the convulsions.  It wasn't a main concern, so he stuck the train of thought back into his head for later reference, for now he had a shivering girl in his arms, undoubtedly just on the verge of shock.<br>Win set her down next to his equipment and wrapped his blanket around the girl.  He reached into his bag and pulled out his first-aid kit.  The old man and other girl were standing behind him.  &quot;Have a seat,&quot; Win pointed down on the floor.  &quot;Here,&quot; he pulled out his thermos of hot coffee and two cups, handing them to the girl.  &quot;Don't worry, I'll have your friend feeling much better in jiffy.&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A> at: 7/22/01 1:16:38 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicchaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gothic chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/22/01 6:20:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> Liz shook her head. These visions she kept having,why were they coming so often? One every two weeks or so was normal,but 3 all in the span of half an hour? She shook her head. That wasn't something she wanted to think about.<br>    She pored the contents of the thermos into the two cups and handed one to Ed. Liz crossed her ankles and drew her knees up to her chest. With one hand she fingered a lock of her waist lenght hair. At the moment it was a wavy tawny brown color,but soon it would become a tangled mess of frizz. Liz sighed. She didn't want to think about that either. She began to nurse her cup of coffee. It was bitter but warm,and the latter 