till,they don't move,but just...sort of stand there...lost in their thoughts. Some people are in such agony..they lost someone or something and they just can't stand it. Others..&quot;Her gaze darted quickly to the man near the coffee machine. She didn't trust him at all.<br>&quot;others are in such a fury. They had something they planned for,something they worked so hard for.And now..they find it was for nothing..its too late. A few of them are just looking up at the things in the sky with a look of wonderment. Their scared and happy at the same time that these things came. I....I don't know where I am,but i think i'm in some sort of trance,just staring up,clueless to everything except whats up there...&quot;Her voice trailed off. The lights of the building hurt her eys so much. Things were fading in and out,Liz was becoming so dizzy...so dizzy... <br>    Liz's head fell forward for a moment and her breathing became frantic.<br> &quot;I can't see barely anything....they don't want me too...this storm isn't natural. I can here the voices now.....they want me to leave this place....we have to get out...its not safe here...its not safe anywhere!We have to..&quot;<br>   Her eyes became clouded over and her forehead rested on her knees. Things weren't making sense..she wasn't there..random thoughts ran through her mind. Lyrics to songs,qoutes,memories...<br> 'liz?'<br> 'yeah mom?'<br> 'up there,to the right,can you see it?That silverish thing?' <br> 'what...what is it..?'<br> 'i don't know..its not round enough to be a balloon,to round to be a plane..'<br> 'its just hovering there..what is it?No one,as far as i can see is aware of it..whats going on?'<br> 'd-don't worry about...we'll be at the hospital soon and then we'll figure everything out there and-'<br> 'but that noise...what is it..?It hurts so much...'<br> 'noise..?I don't here anything...'<br> 'its saying something..i don't know what..it hurts...why won't it stop..?'<br> 'don't worry...we'll be at the hospital soon...everything will be fine..everything will be normal..'<br>  That memory,that was the worst of them. Liz's mother had been driving her to the hospital for...what had it been?She couldn't remeber..oh yeah,a catscan. As they were driving they had seen something in the sky,but..it seemed only they could see it. Liz knew her mother was a bit pyschic,as was her grandmother,and her great grandmother,and her great great...But the noise...Liz's mother couldn't hear it..or she didn't want to..The noise..someone or something was saying something..but she didn't know what..<br> Her head snapped up,her vision clearing. She looked around nervously and her breathing became erratic. After a moment she settled down a bit to be able to speak.<br>  &quot;these things i'm seeing..there not from here...they're from somewhere far away....I don't know..its all to much..&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubeige.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beige</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/23/01 11:50:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.livejournal.com/userpic/67453 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> The rain and wind was really getting fierce now, howling and wailing like a soul in turmoil. Special Agent Lowrey shook the sleepiness out of his eyes, trying to concentrate on the road.<br>&quot;Uh, Vick?&quot; his partner said. &quot;Maybe we should pull over.. or get away from the friggin storm or something.&quot;<br>Vick Lowrey stalwartly ignored his partner's valid concerns and maintained his silence. Taking another long gulp from the cup of expresso, he wiped his mouth and tried to put it down. <br>&quot;Fine.&quot; Ross, the slightly overweight gentleman next to him, had recently joined the Bureau and wasn't quite used to the way things worked. The papers concerning the case were scattered around the car as he tried to study them. &quot;So why are we looking for this girl?&quot;<br>Vick grunted. &quot;I told you a thousand times already. This.. will be the LAST time.. got it?&quot;<br>&quot;Alright. Trust me, I'll remember.&quot;<br>&quot;Elizabeth... something... can't pronounce the last name, oh, it's not important anyway.&quot; Ross felt a bit of satisfaction at his partner's lapse. After all, he was usually so efficient about everything, and Vick never hesitated to rub that in his face.<br>&quot;She's wanted by some upper muckety-muck as a witness. Apparently she was indirectly involved in some hula.. hubla.. hulbaloo...&quot; Vick took a  long draught from the cup. &quot;Bah, I forget. All I know is that it has to do with another one of those psychos from Special Projects, and they always get priority for some reason.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usempaisloan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SempaiSloan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/23/01 11:56:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> A loud crash rattled the suspended ceiling tiles, and the lights flickered. Deuce felt a grin inch onto his face, but it melted as the lights regrouped.<br><br>His instincts were prickling. There was something very wrong with this storm. Usually, he enjoyed all the sturm and drang... but this felt deeply disturbing. <br><br>Six years ago, Deuce had a job in Denmark, and he had to charter a Norwegian fishing trawl to take him back to the UK. They had a squall take them over on the North Sea. Freezing mists of surf threatened to toss the bucket, but Deuce had stood his ground, watching the scene from his portal. He had never felt so alive before. Storms didn't scare him.<br><br>But he was getting uneasy.<br><br>Keeping his head low, he glanced up at the swimsuit girl. Some schmuck was kneeling in front of her, holding fingers up behind his head.<br><br>&quot;Jesus kissing Mary!&quot;<br><br>Was there something in the water in this town?<br><br>A slim man in an argyle sweater wandered over to the coffee maker. He took a quick sip and grimaced.<br><br>&quot;Oh, god!&quot;<br><br>Deuce chuckled. &quot;Pretty fabulous, isn't it?&quot;<br><br>&quot;It's crap. But it's warm.&quot;<br><br>Deuce nodded blandly.<br><br>&quot;So, you from Waatch?&quot;<br><br>Deuce felt his lips tighten. &quot;No.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Here for the Crab Festival?&quot;<br><br>&quot;No.&quot;<br><br>The argyle man seemed to feel snubbed, and attended to his coffee, loading it heavily with creamer. Deuce felt his eyes on him. He looked up at argyle.<br><br>The man was staring at the fold in his coat... a fold that revealed his piece.<br><br>Deuce fought back a snarl.<br><br>&quot;Relax, buddy.&quot; Deuce reached into his other pocket and pulled out his wallet for the stiffening local.<br><br>When he let his wallet fall open, the man visibly relaxed.<br><br>Argyle whispered, &quot;FBI, huh?&quot;<br><br>Deuce slapped his wallet shut and slipped it back into his coat.<br><br>Argyle closed in. &quot;You here for... you know. The old man?&quot;<br><br>Deuce broke eye contact.<br><br>The local continued, &quot;Because, you know... everyone knows about him. His 'friends' from Mexico. His 'other business'.&quot;<br><br>Deuce responded with warmth, &quot;Nothing personal, buddy, but please go about your business.&quot;<br><br>Argyle winked, nodded, and returned to a group of washed out locals.<br><br>Deuce looked to the other side of the room. Swimsuit girl was watching him again... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showMessageRange?topicID=249.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showMessageRange?topicID=249.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showMessageRange?topicID=249.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showMessageRange?topicID=249.topic&start=81&stop=92>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showPrevMessage?topicID=249.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showNextMessage?topicID=249.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.emailToFriend?topicID=249.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.threadControl?topicID=249.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=249.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=249.t